<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="ComparisonOperatorUsageSniff.php" src="/usr/local/pear/share/pear/PHP/CodeSniffer/Standards/Squiz/Sniffs/Operators/ComparisonOperatorUsageSniff.php"><scope doc="A Sniff to enforce the use of IDENTICAL type operators rather than EQUAL operators.&#10;&#10;The use of === true is enforced over implicit true statements,&#10;for example:&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;if ($a)&#10;{&#10;    ...&#10;}&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;should be:&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;if ($a === true)&#10;{&#10;    ...&#10;}&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;It also enforces the use of === false over ! operators.&#10;&#10;@category  PHP&#10;@package   PHP_CodeSniffer&#10;@author    Greg Sherwood &lt;gsherwood@squiz.net&gt;&#10;@author    Marc McIntyre &lt;mmcintyre@squiz.net&gt;&#10;@copyright 2006-2012 Squiz Pty Ltd (ABN 77 084 670 600)&#10;@license   https://github.com/squizlabs/PHP_CodeSniffer/blob/master/licence.txt BSD Licence&#10;@version   Release: 1.4.6&#10;@link      http://pear.php.net/package/PHP_CodeSniffer" ilk="class" interfacerefs="PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniff" line="49" lineend="208" name="Squiz_Sniffs_Operators_ComparisonOperatorUsageSniff"><variable attributes="public" citdl="array" doc="A list of tokenizers this sniff supports.&#10;&#10;@var array" line="60" name="supportedTokenizers" /><variable attributes="private static" citdl="array" doc="A list of valid comparison operators.&#10;&#10;@var array" line="75" name="_validOps" /><variable attributes="private static" citdl="array" doc="A list of invalid operators with their alternatives.&#10;&#10;@var array(int =&gt; string)" line="92" name="_invalidOps" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Registers the token types that this sniff wishes to listen to.&#10;&#10;@return array" ilk="function" line="100" lineend="108" name="register" returns="array" signature="array register()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Process the tokens that this sniff is listening for.&#10;&#10;@param PHP_CodeSniffer_File $phpcsFile The file where the token was found.&#10;@param int                  $stackPtr  The position in the stack where the token&#10;                                       was found.&#10;&#10;@return void" ilk="function" line="120" lineend="205" name="process" signature="void process(PHP_CodeSniffer_File $phpcsFile, int $stackPtr)"><variable citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer_File" ilk="argument" line="120" name="phpcsFile" /><variable citdl="int" ilk="argument" line="120" name="stackPtr" /><variable citdl="array()" line="172" name="data" /><variable citdl="tokens" line="166" name="type" /><variable citdl="int" line="162" name="requiredOps" /><variable citdl="int" line="130" name="i" /><variable citdl="tokens" line="153" name="start" /><variable citdl="phpcsFile.findPrevious()" line="126" name="end" /><variable citdl="int" line="163" name="foundOps" /><variable citdl="phpcsFile.tokenizerType" line="123" name="tokenizer" /><variable citdl="string" line="168" name="error" /><variable citdl="phpcsFile.getTokens()" line="122" name="tokens" /></scope></scope></scope>